# SSH config for remote commands

When running SSH or SCP commands from the workspace (e.g. to bastion, conN, disN), always use:

```bash
ssh -F ~/.aba/ssh.conf <host> "..."
scp -F ~/.aba/ssh.conf ...
```

This suppresses "Warning: Permanently added ... to the list of known hosts" noise and applies standard connection settings (no host key checking, /dev/null known_hosts, 15s timeout, batch mode, ERROR log level).

The config file lives at `~/.aba/ssh.conf` on bastion (the workspace host).
